Acerinox, Iliad SA, LVMH, RCS, Telefonica, Unipol: European Equity Preview

-- B y   I n y o u n g   H w a n g
-- 
2011-06-12T23:32:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-12/iliad-lvmh-rcs-telefonica-unipol-may-be-active-european-stock-preview.html
The following companies’ shares may
be active in European trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  The Stoxx  Europe  600 Index declined 1.3 percent to 268.13.
The Stoxx 50 Index fell 1.3 percent to 2,508.77. The Euro Stoxx
50 Index, a benchmark for nations using the euro, dropped 1.6
percent to 2,732.54.  Acerinox SA (ACX)  : The world’s largest stainless-steel
producer said in a filing it will carry out a reorganization to
make its structure more “coherent” by allowing its operational
businesses to develop through units. The shares fell 1.05
percent to 12.26 euros.  Allianz SE (ALV)  : Allianz Leben’s holdings of  government
bonds  from Portugal, Ireland,  Greece  and  Spain  amounts to less
than 0.3 percent of the insurers’ total investments, Allianz
Leben investment chief, Joerg Ladwein, said in an interview with
 Welt am Sonntag . The shares added 1.2 percent to 92.27 euros.  Air France-KLM (AF)  Group: Europe’s biggest airline said
an open-ended strike by ground maintenance staff may disrupt
some flights to and from Paris. The shares declined 1.4 percent
to 10.56 euros.  Banca Popolare di Milano Scrl (BP IM): The Italian bank’s
lending is in line with requests from the Bank of Italy, General
Manager Enzo Chiesa told  Il Sole 24 Ore  in an interview. The
shares were unchanged at 1.59 euros.  BP Plc (BP/ LN): The London-based oil producer needs to
improve its offer for Russian state-run oil company OAO Rosneft
if it wants to revive a share swap and Arctic exploration deal,
the Financial Times reported, citing Russian Deputy Prime
Minister  Igor Sechin . The shares fell 1.8 percent to 442.05
pence.  Iliad SA (ILD)  : The French broadband services provider
may open the country’s fourth mobile-phone network as soon as
October, Le Figaro said. The shares dropped 0.2 percent to 88.06
euros.  LVMH Moet Hennessy Louis Vuitton SA (MC)  : LVMH’s Sephora
cosmetics brand said it acquired another 20 percent of  Russia ’s
Ile de Beaute, raising its stake to 65 percent. The shares fell
1.8 percent to 114.80 euros.  London Stock Exchange Group Plc (LSE LN):  TMX Group Inc.
should give shareholders more time to vote on a proposed
acquisition by London Stock Exchange Group Plc, said Luc
Bertrand, a spokesman for Maple Group, which is also vying to
buy TMX.      Separately, Desjardins Financial Group, Dundee
Capital Markets Inc., GMP Capital Inc. and Manulife Financial
Corp. joined the group of Canadian banks and pension funds
seeking to buy TMX in a proposal to rival a takeover by the
 London Stock Exchange Group Plc (LSE) , according to a statement from
the Maple Group Acquisition Corp. LSE’s shares dropped 0.2
percent to 943.5 pence.  RCS MediaGroup SpA (RCS)  : Diego Della Valle, chief
executive officer of  Tod’s SpA (TOD)  , aims to increase the
company’s stake in RCS MediaGroup SpA to as much as 20 percent,
Il Sole 24 Ore said, without saying where it got the
information. RCS gained 0.3 percent to 1.204 euros. Tod’s lost 2
percent to 87.30 euros.  Telefonica SA (TEF)  : Europe’s second-largest telecom
operator said in a filing that it suspended its initial public
offering for Atento Inversiones & Teleservicios SA due to
“unfavorable market conditions.” The stock fell 1.49 percent
to 16.19 euros.        Unipol Gruppo Finanziario SpA (UNI)  : The Italian insurer
has no plans to increase its capital, Il Sole 24 Ore said,
citing an interview with Chief Executive Officer Carlo Cimbri.
The shares fell 1.2 percent to 41.41 cents.  To contact the reporter on this story:
